               Pauline",
  abstract  = "The copper-catalyzed reductive Ireland-Claisen rearrangement of
               propargylic acrylates led to 3,4-allenoic acids. The use of
               silanes or pinacolborane as stoichiometric reducing agents and
               triethylphosphite as a ligand facilitated the divergent and
